The paper discusses the problem of extracting useful content from a massive amount of data available on the web, which is a common issue in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and the lack of standard data models and structures (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper proposes a methodology for knowledge extraction that involves configurable and extendible components, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
